ZCZC EE17
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 142300 UTC
LOW PRESSURE 982 WILL BE SITUATED TO THE NW OF THE UK ON WEDNESDAY EVENING
AND WILL CONTINUE TO FILL AND MOV NWARDS. A TRANSIENT RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE
WILL EXTEND ACROSS THE UK DURING THURSDAY. MEANWHILE A DEEP AREA OF LOW
PRESSURE WILL BECOME SITUATED OVER THE MID-ATLANTIC ON THURSDAY AND WILL
REMAIN IN SITU DURING FRIDAY WHICH WILL SLWY MOV NWARDS TO BE CENTRED TO
THE NW OF THE UK ON SATURDAY. A STRG SW FLOW WILL EXTEND ACROSS ALL NITON
SEA AREAS DURING WEDNESDAY EVENING WHICH IS EXP TO PERSIST OVERNIGHT AND
INTO THURSDAY. STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY TO PERSIST ACROSS ALL NITON AREAS ON
FRIDAY WITH OCCASIONAL GALES LIKELY ESPECIALLY OVER ATLANTIC SEA AREAS
AND PROBABLY EXTENDING UP INTO FASTNET LUNDY AND IRISH SEA. WINDS ARE EXP
TO GRADUALLY MOD DURING SATURDAY ESPECIALLY OVER SERNMOST NITON SEA AREAS
